Musicians, your travel experience is about to be revolutionized! Forget about lugging heavy and awkward cases, or putting your precious instrument at risk with soft bags. The Kapsule is a sleek, wearable, rollable, and tech-loaded "all-in-one" musician's luggage!Why did we design the Kapsule?

Soft gig bags, while comfortable, don’t offer enough protection to check in.

Hard cases are good for checking in, but they’re a pain to lug around, they’re heavy and definitely not designed to be worn comfortably, if at all.
Both typically have very limited storage, and you almost always have to bring a 2nd roller or duffle bag for your clothes and toiletries.
So we took the benefits of all these and fused them together into one amazing bag that not only holds your guitar and accessories, but also packs your clothes enough for a 2- to 3-day trip! 
// Protect Your Axe
Trust your instrument to be well-protected in the Kapsule's tough polycarbonate shell. A thick layer of lightweight expanded polystyrene made of 98% air has excellent shock absorbency and insulation to keep your guitar or bass safe. The front of the Kapsule has a massive storage area of any gig bag for your tour-essential gear.
// Consolidate Your Luggage
You may also use that space to pack your clothes and leave your roller luggage at home. With 17+ liters of cargo space, there's enough room for a 2- to 3-day trip. Add our compression packing cubes (stretch goal #2) and you can fit nearly double!
 
​// Save Your Back With Wheels
Our snap-on wheels will make longer walks a breeze, and attaches in seconds without any tools.
 ​// Prevent Headstock DamageThe Kapsule's unique Iso Chamber minimizes the risk of headstock damage by keeping it suspended and isolated.
// Practice Anywhere
Want the freedom to practice anywhere, anytime? Our optional PLAY package is powered by our micro headphone amp small enough to fit in your hand! Simply plug in your headphones and audio player to practice privately. Enjoy dynamic hi-fidelity sound from the nearly-weightless amp, designed by world-renowned audiophile engineer Phil Jones. A 10-foot instrument cable and a 3.5mm auxiliary cable are also included.
// Keep It Charged
Staying productive on the go is easier with your devices charged! Our POWER package features our Oktane wireless power bank (10,000mAh) and two Oktane charging cables (one 6-inch and one 4-foot) with your choice of Apple Lightning or Micro USB. 
// 1 Year Free Peace Of Mind
We’re introducing our industry-first Global Recovery Tag (powered by HomingPIN) for peace of mind while you travel, integrated in over 2800 airports. When a baggage handler finds your bag, they simply type in your unique tag number into their lost-and-found system and you’ll receive a text message and email. A fellow travel can also simply scan the QR code, enter the tag number, and you'll be notified immediately. Service is free for one year upon activation.Using the anonymous tag number instead of a traditional luggage tag will also help protect your identity while you travel. 
// Find Your Kapsule By Voice
As our first stretch goal we’re enabling our voice-controlled Bluetooth Tracker (via Google Assistant, Amazon Alexa, or Apple's Siri) as an add-on option for your Kapsule, complete with an iOS or Android app (powered by Chipolo). The tracker will not only help you find your Kapsule, but also lets you see its last location if it's out of range.  
// Fight Humidity Damage
Avoid costly repairs of hairline cracks and warping due to humidity changes. We teamed up with Boveda to include two-way humidity control, a must-have for any guitar or bass. Place the humidity packs in the built-in pockets to maintain the optimal level of humidity for your instrument. Your Kapsule will come pre-packaged with a FREE Boveda humidity pack and pouch.​// Lock Down Your Guitar
Finally, your Kapsule comes with an industry-standard TSA lock to secure your instrument. Set your 3-digit code and only authorized airport security will be able to open your bag.   

// First Impressions




 
Meet the TeamWe're a passionate bunch over at Gruv Gear, and we've been creating truly innovative and ground-breaking products since our start in 2010—Nearly every product we've launched is patented or patent pending! We strive to build fresh new inventions that make life easier, whether it's for musicians, photographers, filmmakers, or the avid jetsetter. We're blessed to have our brand and products distributed in over 55 countries to date, and we ship worldwide from our warehouses in California, Shanghai, Germany, and Canada.Left to right: Jay, Janeth, Jason, Prince, Victoria, Jeff, and Peter.
Project ChallengesWe've prepared well for this project and have most of the design done, materials selected, and 3D specs ready to go. One of the main challenges we're facing is the uncertainty of costs with our factories due to recent import tax negotiations between USA and China, and ensuring we lock down reasonable costs to support our planned retail pricing. Another challenge is the required funds and efforts to produce multiple size Kapsules, as minimum order quantities have also been rising. If we don't reach certain stretch goals, however, we still aim to build all models but with a staggered timeline. Your contribution and help to spread the word to other musicians will all help to create momentum and success for the Kapsule project, so please share our photos and videos on social media and through word-of-mouth so together we can help revolutionize travel!
